Halong Bay with Indochina Sail Cruise
There are just so many junks to choose for Halong Bay Cruise ranging from US$80 to US$200 but after reading the advice from trip advisor, we have decided to go ahead with Indochina Sail at the rate of US$189 per person for 2D1N. I must say we were very impressed with the service provided by Indochina sail. Everything was booked online directly with them and payment was safe through visa. They picked us up in a very comfortable 10 seater van and the journey was around 3.5 hours. Upon arrival, you're invited to rest at their own waiting lounge while waiting to board the junk. Their services were great and the guide speaks good English. We told them that we're celebrating our Anniversary and they have upgraded us to their deluxe cabin and a bouquet of flowers were arranged upon our arrival. We also met great friends from all over the world and the kayaking was really fun although the weather was cold. The food was also well served and I can say it's delicious! The cabin was clean and the junk was beautiful since it's relatively new (2008). If you're looking for memorable Halong Bay cruise, pay for Indochina as at the end of the trip, you will bring back a memorable trip and more friends, just like we did. Well done, Indochina Sail!
Written March 19, 2010
