6
The beauty is gone
Feb 2019 ‚Ä¢ Couples
What we thought would be a highlight of our Vietnam trip, Halong Bay, was just the opposite. People who visited in past years would not recognize it. Fishing villages have been cleared out and construction companies are building thousands of concrete units lining all sides of the bay, plus casinos and amusement parks.The islands are still there, but the bay itself is full of boats, most in disrepair, following one right after another. The pictures you see have been tailored to show one boat not the hundreds that cruise in every direction.
Written March 11, 2019
kashyap
guwahati59 contributions
4
Beautiful
Dec 2018 ‚Ä¢ Family
Had read a few reviews about how full of oil, floating plastic waste and the heavy presence of other cruise ships have spoilt the charm of the Bay for some visitors. Well, maybe a very occasional plastic bottle ? A speck in the vast blue/green? I did look out for oil but was too distracted by the mystical beauty of my surroundings to notice that. As for the presence of other ships, how about going to see St. Mark's Square, Venice, through the throngs of people? enjoy the Bamboo forest, Arashiyama? One has to be able to look beyond the mundane at what matters. Sailing along the Bay it is absolutely possible to enjoy viewing individual limestone islands or ranges of them without hindrance. And watching them against the setting sun and the mist is out of this world. I would recommend seeing the Bay and judging for oneself instead of restricting oneself to the views of somebody else.
Yes, a lot of hotels being constructed, but that is on the mainland BEFORE one sets out sailing out.
As with every other popular tourist attraction in every other part of the world , authorities do have to place restrictions on activities that are not sustainable.
Written February 9, 2019
D0rHa
Hong Kong, China113 contributions
If you take care a little bit, you'll have a nice day
Take care of the following:
1. If you drive on the highway, it's 2 hours from Hanoi, but if they take you on the ordinary roads, it's 4 hours. If you make a 1day trip, usually you have a 4hours program on the lake (boating, lunch, caves, boating again). If you have to travel twice 4 hours, it doesn't make sense. If you travel twice 2 hours, it's ok. Ask the tourist agent not only the length of the trip, because they will say that "we'll, it depends on the traffic, blablabla". Ask directly if you will be taken on the highway.
2. Be on alert and check where you are taken and if you see that you are not taken on the highway, as agreed, do not hesitate to contact your agent immediately. We were taken on an ordinary road, not the highway. I called the agent and told her that we are very angry and we feel being cheated. She called the boss of the driver and called me back. When she called me back, the boss of the driver called the driver and soon we were on the highway. It took 3 hours, because we lost the first hour, we didn't call the agent quick enough, but on the way back they didn't even try this trick and the trip back to Hanoi was less than 2 hours.
2. Make sure you have a phone number where you can reach the agent if needed. After payment, I was given a phone number, but it did not work.
Luckily, I had another number too, the number of the lady, with whom I was in contact from the beginning by email. I got the number accidentally: the email didn't work from China, where I live, so I asked for her WhatsApp contact. I was given her phone number so that we can contact by WhatsApp. If I don't ask for her WhatsApp contact, I don't have any number I can call. So, if you are given a phone number, call it to make sure it works.
Otherwise the Haling Bay is beautiful, the tours are organised correctly, everyone is very kind, the food is gorgeous, etc.
Written December 25, 2018
gatocanada
London, UK305 contributions
Read this for short highway trip and more...
Sep 2018 ‚Ä¢ Couples
Be aware that there is a new highway to Halong Bay cutting the time almost in half, but just a few tour operators are using it. Make sure to book your day tour with one that offers the drive on this new road, otherwise you will be 9 hours sitting on o a uncomfortable bus. Also for more money try to pick a tour with limousine bus or van, the bus only has 3 seats per row and the van 2 seats, seats are very confortable and lots of leg room, the regular buses are a torture!! no leg room, impossible to recline seat, very narrow seats, etc, etc.
Reason for tours not using new road probably is that they will not have the break stop set up, I mean that on the long road there is an stop on a huge craft shop and souvenir store where all the drivers and guides get free meal for stoping there, so my guess is that on the new road there is no this kind of stop yet, and also if all tours take the new road this stores will go out of business.
Another thing if you pick the tour with Ti Top island, don't bother to choose the swim instead of climbing the hill, the beach is pretty small and there is nothing special, jelly fish only!!. Way better to climb the hill and the view from the top is amazing.
Another thing, there is an option for kayacking or bamboo boat, the boat ride will take like 10 minutes only, but if you choose the kayac, you can take like 30 minutes on your own.
One more thing, if are planning on a 2 day tour, consider doing a 1 day only and on the other day do a Ninh Binh tour.
Written September 24, 2018
Lara981
Amsterdam, The Netherlands94 contributions
Loss of Magic...
Oct 2017 ‚Ä¢ Friends
We really wanted to go to Halong Bay for the breathtaking nature. We arranged a cruise on a boat via one of our hostels and were really excited to go. Getting to the boat everything was still great; enough space and good beds to sleep in. The boat is a little old, but in a charming way.
As you arrive the first thing you see is that it seems that all tourists in Vietnam are gathered in one place. Then you take off and all the same boats drive the waters with a million canon camera‚Äôs, creating an extremely touristic view inside of Halong Bay.
It seems all cruises have the same schedule; lunch, which is mainly Western, because it seems they think this is all we eat. Then you can relax on the boat and take in a bit of Halong Bay, which is cool. But then the queuing begins at the ‚ÄúSurprising Cave‚Äù. All the tourists are gathered on the same stairs and it‚Äôs a waiting game for when to move on. The cave itself is beautiful, but the magic is taken out of it by the many people that are being squeezed through the same pathway at once.
Then you go to the little beach and you have the great view over halong bay at the peak. We didn‚Äôt even bother to go up, because we were so fed up with the queuing and all the people that are on the same pathway.
Then it‚Äôs back to the boat for a spring roll snack, which was really nice and fun to roll! This probably varies per cruise.
Then dinner came with almost only fried stuff; chicken nuggets, fries, fried fish and some rice. The evening however was great, because we had a fun group, so we ended up drinking and laughing together. Next morning kayaking at 6.30 for some exercise before breakfast, which was fun to do alongside the bay. Then we had breakfast, again Western, to then go to the pearl farm; another touristic attraction with an expensive pearl shop.
All and all this was really not our thing and quite frankly a waste of our money; the cruise was around 100 USD per person for which you get a return bus ride (3,5 hrs) from Hanoi to Halong city, 1x breakfast, 2x lunch, 1x dinner, drinks are not included and are almost twice the price as on mainland. We don‚Äôt think the cruise is too expensive for what you get, but we had higher expectations of the whole experience. The nature is amazing, but the magic is completely lost by the many tourists and the commerciality around the area.
Written October 18, 2017
